This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on language acquisition and the ability of unsupervised neural networks to apply linguistic rules. It also draws from the literature on determiner/noun productivity, which is a topic within computational linguistics. 

The paper also involves the use of deep learning, which makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Additionally, the paper involves the use of autoencoder networks, which are a type of neural network commonly used in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves the application of deep learning to cognitive science, which could potentially place it in the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
